@startuml oms-test-execution

title HIL Test Execution Flow - OMS Board

actor       "Developer"                     as Dev
participant "OMS Repo\nGitHub"              as GH
participant "OMS Repo CI\nGitHub Actions"   as CI
participant "Artifactory"                   as ART
participant "Raspberry Pi\nHIL Controller"  as RPi
participant "OpenOCD\nSerial Debug Probe"   as OCD
participant "MCP4922 DAC\n(SPI)"            as DAC
participant "USB-CAN FD Adapter"            as CAN
participant "OMS Board\n(DUT)"              as DUT

== trigger ==

Dev -> GH   : git push origin develop
GH -> CI    : push event on develop via webhook
CI -> CI    : build firmware ELF (CM7)
CI -> ART   : upload ELF file with tag & commit SHA
CI -> RPi   : notify new firmware available\nArtifactory URL + commit SHA
RPi -> ART  : download ELF file
ART --> RPi : ELF file

== board fixture - setup ==

RPi -> OCD  : openocd program ELF file verify reset
OCD -> DUT  : flash ELF via SWD/JTAG
OCD --> RPi : Verified OK

RPi -> DAC  : set all analog outputs = 0 V ambient via SPI
RPi -> RPi  : set all outputs = LOW via GPIO
RPi -> CAN  : open can1 (FDCAN2) via flush queue

RPi -> OCD  : openocd reset run
OCD -> DUT  : execute from reset vector

DUT -> CAN  : OMS board status 0x140A [periodic] via FDCAN2
CAN --> RPi : recv 0x140A via board alive

note over RPi : OMS alive confirmed

== test body - token / flow control ==

note over RPi,DUT : HIL impersonates Control Board on FDCAN2

RPi -> CAN  : can1.send() via token request frame 0x1804
CAN -> DUT  : token request 0x1804 via FDCAN2
DUT -> CAN  : token grant frame 0x1403 via FDCAN2
CAN --> RPi : recv_matching(0x1403, timeout=2s)
RPi -> RPi  : assert token granted

== test body - selector valve ==

RPi -> CAN  : can1.send() via selector valve command frame 0x1800
CAN -> DUT  : set selector valve 0x1800 via FDCAN2
DUT -> CAN  : selector valve response frame 0x1400 via FDCAN2
CAN --> RPi : recv_matching(0x1400, timeout=2s)
RPi -> RPi  : assert valve position

== test body - filter pump ==

RPi -> CAN  : can1.send() via filter pump command frame 0x1802
CAN -> DUT  : filter pump control 0x1802 via FDCAN2
DUT -> CAN  : filter pump response frame 0x1401 via FDCAN2
CAN --> RPi : recv_matching(0x1401, timeout=2s)
RPi -> RPi  : assert pump state

== test body - drain valve ==

RPi -> CAN  : can1.send() via drain valve command frame 0x1801
CAN -> DUT  : drain valve control 0x1801 via FDCAN2
DUT -> CAN  : drain valve response frame 0x1402 via FDCAN2
CAN --> RPi : recv_matching(0x1402, timeout=2s)
RPi -> RPi  : assert drain valve state

== test body - ADC / analog stimulus ==

RPi -> DAC  : inject analog signal via SPI
DAC -> DUT  : analog voltage via ADC input
note over DUT : stimulus only (no immediate CAN response)
DUT -> CAN  : telemetry frame via FDCAN2
CAN --> RPi : recv_matching(telemetry COB-ID, timeout=2s)
RPi -> RPi  : assert ADC reading within range

== test body - token release ==

RPi -> CAN  : can1.send() via token release frame 0x1805
CAN -> DUT  : release control 0x1805 via FDCAN2
DUT -> CAN  : token release ack frame 0x1404 via FDCAN2
CAN --> RPi : recv_matching(0x1404, timeout=2s)
RPi -> RPi  : assert token released

== board fixture - teardown ==

RPi -> RPi  : GPIO · all outputs → LOW
RPi -> DAC  : all outputs → 0 V via SPI close
RPi -> CAN  : can1 · close
RPi -> OCD  : openocd reset run · leave board in reset

RPi --> CI  : pytest-html + JUnit XML via exit code
CI -> GH    : report results via pass/fail status on commit

@enduml
